All 8 pages: viewport meta ✅, mobile-fixes.css imported ✅.

Here's what was done and why each issue is now fixed:

---

**Created `public/mobile-fixes.css`** — shared across all 8 pages, imported just before `</head>`. Rules only fire at `≤768px`, so desktop is untouched.

**What it fixes:**

| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| `.data-table` / `.target-table` overflow | `display:block; overflow-x:auto` — tables scroll horizontally instead of breaking layout |
| `.card` padding (wieser-buyside: `35px 40px`) | Reduced to `20px` on mobile |
| `.header` padding (wieser-buyside: `45px 50px`) | Reduced to `24px 16px` on mobile |
| `.gate` top margin (`100px auto`) | Reduced to `32px auto` + `width: calc(100% - 32px)` |
| `.gate input[type="email"]` | `font-size: 16px` — prevents iOS zoom on tap |
| Multi-column grids (valuation, levers, fee, phase, toc-list, grid2/3/4) | All collapse to `1fr` on mobile |
| Inline `grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr` styles (ebitda-levers page) | Overridden with attribute selector + `!important` |
| `.slider-row` with number input | Stacks vertically, input goes full-width |
| `.attack-pipeline` (4 columns) | Collapses to 1 column, arrows hidden |
| `.match-counter` | Stacks vertically |
| `.cta-btn` | Full-width, 44px+ tap target |
| Checkbox labels | `min-height: 44px` touch target |
| Inline flex rows in EBITDA lever cards | `flex-wrap: wrap` via attribute selector |
| Very small screens (480px) | Font size bump, snapshot grid collapses to 1-col |
